primary.description: The configuration of the site’s primary tunnel
primary.name: primary

destinationType.description: The destination type of the IPsec tunnel
destinationType.name: destinationType

publicCatoIpId.description: The ID of the public IP (Allocated IP) of the Cato PoP to which the tunnel will connect. This will be the source-IP of the traffic transmitted to the Cato cloud over this tunnel when egressing the Cato Cloud
publicCatoIpId.name: publicCatoIpId

lastMileBw.description: The maximum allowed bandwidth for the site. If not specified, it will be set according to the site license. If the ISP provided bandwidth is below the site bandwidth, set this parameter to the ISP bandwidth or below
lastMileBw.name: lastMileBw

downstream.description: The maximum downstream bandwidth from the Cato Cloud to the site, in Mbps. This value can be used for capping the downstream traffic. It should not be set above the ISP downstream bandwidth or the site license bandwidth.
downstream.name: downstream

upstream.description: The maximum upstream bandwidth, in Mbps. The Cato Cloud cannot cap this direction, and this setting is used as a best-effort indication by the Cato Cloud.
upstream.name: upstream

privateCatoIp.description: Cato’s private IP, used for BGP routing. Applicable for sites using BGP only
privateCatoIp.name: privateCatoIp

privateSiteIp.description: Site private IP, used for BGP routing. Applicable for sites using BGP only
privateSiteIp.name: privateSiteIp

psk.description: Pre-shared key. This field is write-only.
psk.name: psk
